# Page control sizing

Match the **← Dashboard** back link (`page-card-back-link`). All buttons and text fields inside page cards must use this compact size.

## Size token (`.page-control`)

- `min-h-8` (32px)
- `px-3 py-1.5`
- `text-xs font-medium`
- `rounded-lg`
- `normal-case tracking-normal`

## CSS classes to use

| Element | Class |
|---------|--------|
| Buttons in page cards | `btn btn-*` inside `.page-card` (auto-sized via `.page-card .btn`) |
| Back / nav pill | `page-card-back-link` |
| Icon + input wrapper | `page-field-wrap` + `page-field-icon` (`w-9`, `text-sm`) |
| Inputs / selects | `page-field-input` inside `.page-card` |
| Standalone inputs | `page-form-input` |
| Master forms | `page-master-form`, `page-master-form-field`, `page-master-form-actions` |

## Do

- Put module UI inside `.page-card` / `.page-card-body` so shared sizing applies.
- Use `page-field-wrap` + `page-field-input` for labeled fields (same height as buttons).
- Use `btn btn-primary` / `btn-success` / `btn-secondary` without extra `text-sm`, `text-xs`, or custom `min-h-*` overrides.
- Keep toolbar actions in `page-toolbar`; list search in `page-field-wrap page-master-search`.

## Don't

- Don't use `min-h-[42px]`, `py-2.5`, or `text-sm` on page-card controls unless explicitly redesigning the system.
- Don't add bordered panels around forms unless requested.
- Don't mix Bootstrap `btn-sm` / inline size overrides that fight `.page-card .btn`.

## Reference

Defined in `frontend/src/App.css`:

```css
.page-control,
.page-card-back-link,
.page-card .btn { min-h-8; px-3 py-1.5; text-xs; ... }

.page-card input.page-field-input,
.page-card select.page-field-input { min-h-8; py-1.5; px-3; text-xs; ... }
```

When adding new pages or forms, follow Cost Center master (`frontend/src/pages/masters/cost-center/`) as the layout reference.
